   {:e #blake3 "a6da5abfa92e5e0e5c790311c79b1051ce020649df41765bce885dde6b45287b" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Currently crash recovery = load all .edn files (O(F) where F=13K+). With WAL + checkpoint, recovery = load checkpoint + replay WAL delta (O(1) + O(k) where k = entries since checkpoint). Three recovery levels: Fast (checkpoint + WAL, O(1)+O(k)), Medium (checkpoint + edn delta, O(1)+O(F-C)), Slow (full edn rebuild, O(F) — fallback). APPROACH: Modify LiveStore::open() or daemon startup (~100 LOC). Recovery sequence: (1) Try checkpoint.bin (renamed from store.bin — see DS-RENAME observation). Deserialize Store. Record checkpoint_lsn from metadata. (2) If WAL exists: read entries since checkpoint_lsn. Validate CRC + chain hash for each. Apply valid entries to Store. (3) For each WAL entry without corresponding .edn file: generate the .edn file (run mini-checkpoint). (4) Ready to serve. CHECKPOINT FORMAT: Extend the existing store.bin format (bincode-serialized Store) with a footer: { checkpoint_lsn: u64, wal_chain_hash: [u8; 32], timestamp: u64 }. The chain_hash at checkpoint time enables verification that the WAL was not tampered between checkpoint and recovery. EDGE CASES: (a) WAL truncated mid-entry: chain hash detects exact truncation. Entries after truncation are lost (never fsynced — client was not notified). (b) Checkpoint corrupt (CRC fail): fall back to Medium recovery (edn delta) or Slow (full rebuild). (c) WAL missing: OK — checkpoint was the latest state. No entries to replay. (d) Both WAL and checkpoint missing: Slow recovery from .edn files (existing behavior, always works). INVARIANT: After recovery, Store = fold(all .edn files) = fold(checkpoint + WAL delta). This is INV-STORE-020 maintained through crash. ACCEPTANCE: (1) Normal restart: checkpoint + 0 WAL entries = instant. (2) Crash after 10 WAL entries: restart recovers all 10. (3) Corrupt WAL: recovers entries before corruption, regenerates .edn for those, ignores tail. (4) Corrupt checkpoint: falls back to edn rebuild, succeeds. FILES: crates/braid/src/live_store.rs (open path), crates/braid-kernel/src/wal.rs (reader). RISK: Checkpoint + WAL delta may diverge from full .edn rebuild if there's a bug in apply_datoms. Add a verification mode: after recovery, compare Store hash against fold(all .edn files) hash." :op :assert}
